CITY OF IRON MOUNTAIN v. WISCONSIN MICHIGAN POWER COMPANY. No. 7592. Circuit Court of Appeals, Sixth Circuit. Oct. 10, 1938. Ray MacAllister, Ray Derham, and Paul Rahm, all of Iron Mountain, Mich., for appellant. Raymond Turner, of Iron Mountain, Mich., and James D. Shaw, of Milwaukee, Wis., for appellee.

Before HICKS, SIMONS, and ALLEN, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

It is ordered that the appeal in this cause be and the same is dismissed, pursuant to stipulation of counsel.
